    "2026-07-02 V9r — Session-swap fail-fast tripwire (paired with V9r-T; pi-integration-contract/session-only-degraded-state.md §Session-swap fail-fast tripwire, host-prerequisites.md clause (a) governed-by-rebind / (b) / (c-i) / (d), diagnostics/code-registry-host.md). Fills the four behaviour-bearing seams in src/extension/session-swap-tripwire.ts and wires the arming into src/extension/session-shutdown.ts. sessionSwapInstanceSurvivedDiagnostic(reason) builds the (E, runtime) diagnostic with details.event.reason = the armed session-only reason and the Message string sourced verbatim from diagnostics/code-registry-host.md (<reason> interpolated, em-dash separator). armSessionSwapTripwireForReason(registry, reason) arms the private per-instance sessionSwapTornDown flag only when isSessionOnlyReason (\"new\"/\"resume\"/\"fork\"), a no-op on \"quit\"/\"reload\" or an unknown coerced reason, idempotent under multi-session_shutdown delivery (clause (b)). guardSessionSwapTripwire(deps) fires only on the ARMED tripwire — emit exactly one loom/host/session-swap-instance-survived via the console.error sink, then fail-fast-terminate (control does not return); a no-op when unarmed (dormant governed-by-rebind steady state). runGuardedSlashHandler(deps, dispatch) runs the guard at entry so an armed tripwire terminates before dispatch ever runs; the Pi-owned /reload is never wrapped and stays unguarded (clause (c-i)). runSessionShutdown calls armSessionSwapTripwireForReason after the full five-sub-step teardown, writing NO degraded branch (no markRuntimeDegraded, no \"degraded-needs-reload\" tag, no session-shutdown-runtime-degraded emission, no degraded slash note). No new diagnostics-registry codes; the guard emission reuses V9g's emitTeardownDiagnostic (its existing allow-broad-catch sites). No module-level mutable state / broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call in src/**. All 13 V9r-T tests green; full suite 1385 green, typecheck + lint + H2a/H3a gates clean.",
    "2026-07-02 V9r-T — Session-swap fail-fast tripwire tests (paired V9r impl; pi-integration-contract/session-only-degraded-state.md §Session-swap fail-fast tripwire, host-prerequisites.md clause (a) governed-by-rebind / (b) / (c-i) / (d), drain-state-contract.md, diagnostics/code-registry-host.md). Extends src/extension/reload-wiring.ts LoomRegistry with the private per-extension-instance tripwire flag + armed reason (trivial armSessionSwapTornDown(reason) writer / readSessionSwapTornDown() reader — NOT part of the public readDrainState surface, adds no readDrainState arm — plus the SessionOnlyReason / SessionSwapTripwireState types), and adds src/extension/session-swap-tripwire.ts — the SESSION_SWAP_INSTANCE_SURVIVED_CODE constant, SESSION_ONLY_REASONS / isSessionOnlyReason predicate, the FailFastTerminator seam (the NFR-2.1 Environment.FailFast-equivalent let-crash path, injected so tests observe termination without exiting) + TripwireGuardDeps, sessionSwapInstanceSurvivedDiagnostic (sentinel stub), armSessionSwapTripwireForReason (no-op stub), guardSessionSwapTripwire (deliberately INVERTED stub — fires on the UNARMED registry and stays dormant on the ARMED one, so both fires-when-armed and dormant-when-unset red), and runGuardedSlashHandler (dispatches WITHOUT guarding). Plus tests/session-swap-tripwire.test.ts with 13 tests, each citing cka-27 / the registry code inline. cka-27 (arming): the three session-only reasons (new/resume/fork) arm the tripwire and record the reason, quit/reload do not, isSessionOnlyReason classifies the two-way partition, and a session-only runSessionShutdown runs the SAME full teardown as quit/reload (drain + watcher close) while arming the flag and writing NO degraded branch (no markRuntimeDegraded, no \"degraded-needs-reload\" tag, no loom/host/session-shutdown-runtime-degraded emission). cka-27 (fires): a guard against an armed tripwire emits exactly one loom/host/session-swap-instance-survived row via the console.error sink then fail-fast-terminates (emission strictly before termination); the guarded slash-handler entry and the session_start body both terminate before dispatch on an armed tripwire. cka-27 (no false positive): a fresh unarmed registry is dormant (no emit, no terminate, no throw), arming is idempotent under a permitted multi-session_shutdown re-arm (one guard -> one row), and an unarmed guarded handler dispatches normally and returns its result (the Pi-owned /reload command, never wrapped by runGuardedSlashHandler, is thus unguarded, clause (c-i)). loom/host/session-swap-instance-survived: the diagnostic is (E, runtime), carries details.event.reason with the armed session-only reason, and its message is sourced from the registry Message column with <reason> interpolated (em-dash separator). No new diagnostics-registry codes (the host row already exists; V9r-T is its first asserting test). Inert/non-compliant stub seam: no module-level mutable state / broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call in src/**; the guard emission reuses V9g's emitTeardownDiagnostic (its existing allow-broad-catch sites). Typecheck + lint (incl. no-broad-catch / no-restricted-syntax / H2a / H3a) clean; 10 of the 13 tests red on their own primary assertions (sentinel diagnostic, absent arming, inverted/absent guard, unguarded dispatch) because the V9r body is absent — fail-red-for-the-intended-reason; the 3 companion tests (negative arming for quit/reload, the isSessionOnlyReason predicate, dormant guarded dispatch) hold as steady-state invariants; the other 1375 tests stay green.",
    "2026-07-01 V4g — Pre-evaluation reload-failure integration (paired with V4g-T; errors-and-results/error-model.md ERR-7, discovery/package-and-settings.md §\"Watcher-time reload failures\"). Wires createReloadFailurePreEvalRouter in src/extension/reload-pre-eval.ts to route each synthetic watcher-time reload failure onto the V7d loom-system-note delivery channel. The router reuses V9b's single ReloadFailureInjector.injectReloadFailure interface (registry-swap and .loom/.warp re-parse arms surfacing loom/runtime/registry-swap-failed; V10d's settings-remerge arm surfacing loom/load/settings-invalid-json), but its emitDiagnostic sink now hands each constructed Diagnostic to emitDiagnosticBatch([diagnostic], channel) instead of dropping it — one loom-system-note per injection carrying the arm's Diagnostic[] in details.diagnostics, delivered through sendSystemNote with the fixed triggerTurn:false option, so no arm fires a turn or becomes an evaluation outcome. No live V10d/V9b watcher is stood up. No new diagnostics-registry codes; no module-level mutable state / broad catch / ambient primitive / Promise combinator / Sync call. All 4 V4g-T tests green; full suite 1372 green, typecheck + lint clean."
